## Conditional Logic

```toml
Show if:
  [Condition 1]
  [Condition 2]
  
Execute if:
  [Condition 1]
  [Condition 2]

Hide if:
  [Condition]

Skip if:
  [Condition]
```

**Condition formats:**
```
Source.path.field: value
Source.path.field > value
Source.path.field < value
Source.path.field >= value
Source.path.field <= value
Source.path.field: one of [option1, option2, option3]
Source.path.field: not empty
Source.path.field: contains "text"
```

## Actions & Behaviors

```toml
[Action ActionName]
Description: What this action accomplishes

Execute if:
  [Conditions under which this runs]

Steps:
  - Step 1 in plain language
  - Step 2 in plain language
  - Step 3 in plain language

On success:
  - What happens when it succeeds

On error:
  - What happens if it fails

Timeout: duration (if applicable)
Retry: yes/no and retry logic
```

**Example:**
```toml
[Action SaveUserProfile]
Description: Saves user profile changes to database

Execute if:
  State.form.hasChanges: yes
  State.form.isValid: yes
  DB.Users.permission: edit

Steps:
  - Collect all form field values
  - Check email format is valid
  - Check required fields are filled
  - Send data to API.users.update endpoint
  - Wait for confirmation

On success:
  - Show message "Profile updated successfully"
  - Set State.form.hasChanges: no
  - Read updated user data from DB.Users

On error:
  - Show error message to user
  - Keep form in edit mode
  - Save error details for logging

Timeout: 10 seconds
Retry: no
```

