Patterns for Convex, React, Next.js, and Tailwind CSS development.

## Data Operations (Convex)

```toml
[Query QueryName]
Description: Fetches data from database (read-only, reactive)

Input parameters:
  paramName: type (description)
  userId: text (User ID to filter by)
  limit: number (Default: 10)

Data source: DB.TableName

Filter by:
  DB.TableName.field: value
  DB.TableName.field > value

Sort by: field name (direction: ascending/descending)

Return: List of items / Single item / Count

Subscribed: yes/no (Auto-updates when data changes)
```

**Example:**
```toml
[Query GetUserTodos]
Description: Fetch all todos for a specific user

Input parameters:
  userId: text (User ID)
  status: text (Options: all, active, completed. Default: all)

Data source: DB.Todos

Filter by:
  DB.Todos.userId: matches input userId
  If status not "all": DB.Todos.status: matches input status

Sort by: createdAt (direction: descending)

Return: List of todos
Subscribed: yes (UI updates when todos change)
```

```toml
[Mutation MutationName]
Description: Creates, updates, or deletes data (write operation)

Input parameters:
  paramName: type (description)

Operation: Create / Update / Delete

When Create:
  Table: DB.TableName
  Set fields:
    field1: value or input parameter
    field2: value or input parameter
    createdAt: current timestamp

When Update:
  Table: DB.TableName
  Find by: DB.TableName.id: matches input id
  Update fields:
    field1: new value
    updatedAt: current timestamp

When Delete:
  Table: DB.TableName
  Find by: DB.TableName.id: matches input id
  
Check before:
  - Check rule 1
  - Check rule 2

On success:
  - Return: created/updated item
  - Trigger: any related updates

On error:
  - Return error: message
```

**Example:**
```toml
[Mutation CreateTodo]
Description: Creates a new todo item for user

Input parameters:
  text: text (Todo description)
  userId: text (User creating the todo)

Operation: Create

Check before:
  - Input text: not empty
  - Input text length < 500 characters
  - DB.Users.id: matches input userId (user exists)

When Create:
  Table: DB.Todos
  Set fields:
    text: input text
    userId: input userId
    status: active
    completed: no
    createdAt: current timestamp

On success:
  - Return: created todo item
  - Notify: user's other tabs (real-time update)

On error:
  - If user not found: Return error "User does not exist"
  - If text empty: Return error "Todo text required"
```

```toml
[Action ActionName]  
Description: Server-side operation (can call external APIs, longer running)

Input parameters:
  paramName: type (description)

Steps:
  - Step 1 using Convex queries/mutations
  - Step 2 calling external API
  - Step 3 processing results

Can access:
  - Convex database via queries/mutations
  - External APIs
  - File storage
  - Third-party services

Timeout: duration
Return: result data
```

**Example:**
```toml
[Action ProcessPayment]
Description: Process payment via Stripe and update order

Input parameters:
  orderId: text (Order to process)
  paymentMethodId: text (Stripe payment method)

Steps:
  - Get order details from DB.Orders via query
  - Do Stripe API call to process payment
  - If payment successful: Update DB.Orders status to "paid"
  - If payment failed: Update DB.Orders status to "failed"
  - Send confirmation email to user

Can access:
  - DB.Orders (via mutations)
  - Stripe API (external)
  - Email service (external)

On success:
  - Return: payment confirmation details
  
On error:
  - Return error with specific failure reason
  - Log error for debugging

Timeout: 30 seconds
```

## React Component Patterns

```toml
[Component ComponentName]
Type: Server / Client
Description: Component purpose and behavior

Rendering: Server-side / Client-side

Props received:
  propName: type (description, required/optional)

Internal state:
  STATE.fieldName: yes/no (Default: no)
  Data field: type (Default: value)

Data fetching:
  Query: QueryName(parameters)
  Subscribed: yes/no

User interactions:
  When [event]:
    - Action description

Styling: Tailwind classes or description

Children: accepts/doesn't accept child components
```

**Example: Client Component**
```toml
[Component TodoList]
Type: Client
Description: Interactive list of user todos with add/edit/delete

Rendering: Client-side (uses hooks and interactivity)

Props received:
  userId: text (User ID to show todos for, required)
  initialFilter: text (Default filter, optional)

Internal state:
  STATE.adding: yes/no (Default: no)
  New todo text: text (Default: empty)
  Filter: text (Default: "all")

Data fetching:
  Query: GetUserTodos(userId, Filter)
  Subscribed: yes (Real-time updates)

User interactions:
  When user clicks "Add Todo":
    - Set STATE.adding: yes
    - Show input field
  
  When user submits new todo:
    - Run Mutation: CreateTodo(New todo text, userId)
    - Set New todo text: empty
    - Set STATE.adding: no
  
  When user clicks delete on todo:
    - Run Mutation: DeleteTodo(todo ID)

Styling: 
  - Container: flex flex-col gap-4 p-4
  - Todos: space-y-2
  - Add button: bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded

Children: doesn't accept
```

**Example: Server Component**
```toml
[Component UserDashboard]
Type: Server
Description: Dashboard showing user stats and recent activity

Rendering: Server-side (no interactivity, faster initial load)

Props received:
  userId: text (User to show dashboard for, required)

Data fetching:
  Query: GetUserStats(userId)
  Query: GetRecentActivity(userId, limit: 10)
  Subscribed: no (Server components don't subscribe)

Displays:
  - User statistics summary
  - Recent activity list
  - Navigation to detailed pages

Styling:
  - Grid layout: grid grid-cols-3 gap-6
  - Cards: bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-6

Children: accepts child components for extensibility
```

## Next.js Routing & Pages

```toml
[Page PageName]
Path: /path/to/page
Type: Server / Client component
Description: Page purpose

Access control:
  Requires: Authentication / Specific role / Public

Params from URL:
  paramName: type (dynamic route segment)

Search params:
  paramName: type (URL query parameter)

Data loading:
  - Read on server / Read on client
  - Data source and queries

SEO metadata:
  Title: page title
  Description: page description
```

**Example:**
```toml
[Page TodoDetailPage]
Path: /todos/[todoId]
Type: Server component (for better SEO and performance)
Description: Shows detailed view of a single todo

Access control:
  Requires: Authentication
  Permission: User must own the todo or be admin

Params from URL:
  todoId: text (Todo ID from URL path)

Data loading:
  - Read on server
  - Query: GetTodoById(todoId)
  - Query: GetTodoComments(todoId)

If todo not found:
  - Show: 404 page

If user lacks permission:
  - Redirect to: /todos
  - Show message: "Access denied"

SEO metadata:
  Title: Todo text (from todo data)
  Description: "View and manage todo: [todo text]"

Displays:
  - Todo details card
  - Comments section
  - Edit/delete buttons (if user has permission)
```

```toml
[API Route RouteName]
