## Complete Example: Translating Complex Code to DSL

### Original Code Context
The 11labsProvider.tsx manages voice and text sessions with ElevenLabs AI. Key challenges:
- Switching between text and voice modes
- Cross-tab session coordination
- Connection state management
- Message queueing
- Timeout handling

### DSL Translation

```toml
[System ElevenLabsProvider]
Description: Manages AI conversations through text and voice channels

Purpose:
  - Enable users to chat with AI via text or voice
  - Coordinate sessions across multiple browser tabs
  - Handle network connections reliably
  - Queue messages when connection is unavailable

[Define SessionMode]
Description: Current mode of AI conversation

Options:
  - idle: No active session
  - text: Text-based chat via WebSocket
  - voice: Voice conversation via WebRTC

Storage: Component state
Default: idle

[Define ConnectionState]
Description: Status of network connection

Options:
  - idle: Not connected
  - connecting: Connection in progress
  - connected: Ready to send/receive
  - disconnected: Connection ended

Storage: Reference (persists during transitions)

[State SessionManagement]
Description: Tracks current session state

Data fields:
  Current mode: SessionMode (Current active mode)
  STATE.transitioning: yes/no (Switching between modes)
  Text connection state: ConnectionState
  Voice connection state: ConnectionState
  Conversation ID: text (Unique session identifier)
  
[State CrossTabCoordination]
Description: Coordinates sessions across browser tabs

Data fields:
  This tab ID: text (Unique identifier for this tab)
  Active tab ID: text (Which tab owns the session)
  STATE.otherTabActive: yes/no (Another tab has active session)
  Other tab mode: SessionMode (What mode other tab is using)

Purpose: Prevents multiple tabs from conflicting sessions
Storage: Browser localStorage with timestamps

[Configuration Timeouts]
Description: Time limits for various operations

Values:
  Text connection timeout: 8 seconds
  Text disconnection timeout: 5 seconds
  Voice connection timeout: 10 seconds
  Text idle auto-close: 5 minutes

[Action StartTextSession]
Description: Begin text-based chat session

Execute if:
  State.SessionManagement.currentMode: idle or voice
  Cross-tab: No other tab has active text session

Steps:
  - Set STATE.transitioning: yes
  - Set Text connection state: connecting
  - Request session from ElevenLabs API
  - Provide conversation history if available
  - Configure WebSocket connection
  - Wait for connection confirmation
  - Set Text connection state: connected
  - Set Current mode: text
  - Set STATE.transitioning: no
  - Acquire cross-tab lock for text mode
  - Notify other tabs of active session
  - Start idle timer (5 minutes)
  - Send all queued messages

On success:
  - User can send text messages
  - Messages flow through WebSocket

On error:
  - Set Current mode: idle
  - Set Text connection state: idle
  - Show error message to user
  - Log error details

Timeout: 8 seconds
Retry: yes (automatic on timeout)

[Action StopTextSession]
Description: End active text session cleanly

Execute if:
  Current mode: text
  Text connection state: connected

Steps:
  - Cancel idle timer
  - Set Text connection state: idle
  - Send end signal to ElevenLabs session
  - Stop monitoring session updates
  - Wait for disconnection confirmation
  - Clear Conversation ID
  - Clear session data from State
  - Release cross-tab lock
  - Notify other tabs session ended

On success:
  - Session cleanly closed
  - Resources released

On error:
  - Force close after timeout
  - Log timeout warning
  - Still release resources

Timeout: 5 seconds
Retry: no

[Action StartVoiceSession]
Description: Begin voice conversation session

Execute if:
  Current mode: idle or text
  Cross-tab: No other tab has active voice session

Pre-steps:
  + Check if text session is active
  + If text session active: Run CleanupTextSession
  + Wait for text cleanup to complete

Steps:
  - Set STATE.transitioning: yes
  - Set Voice connection state: connecting
  - Request session from ElevenLabs API
  - Provide conversation history if available
  - Configure WebRTC connection
  - Wait for connection confirmation
  - Set Voice connection state: connected
  - Set Current mode: voice
  - Set STATE.transitioning: no
  - Acquire cross-tab lock for voice mode
  - Notify other tabs of active session
  - Send all queued messages

On success:
  - User can speak with AI
  - Audio flows through WebRTC

On error:
  - If error is: another session active
    - Try fast cleanup of text session
    - Retry voice session start once
  - If still fails:
    - Set Current mode: idle
    - Set Voice connection state: idle
    - Show error message to user

Timeout: 10 seconds (first attempt), 5 seconds (retry)
Retry: yes (automatic once with text cleanup)

[+ Add Action CleanupTextSession]
Description: Explicitly cleanup text session before mode switch

Execute if:
  Text connection state: connected
  Purpose: switching to voice mode

Steps:
  - Set Text connection state: idle immediately
  - Send end signal to text session
  - Stop monitoring text session updates  
  - Wait for disconnection confirmation
  - Clear text session data

On success:
  - Text session fully closed
  - Ready to start voice session

On error:
  - Force close after timeout
  - Log warning
  - Proceed anyway

Timeout: 1.5 seconds
Retry: no
Critical: yes (must complete before voice starts)

[Action SendTextMessage]
Description: Send a text message to AI

Execute if:
  Current mode: text or voice

Behavior when mode is voice:
  - Check if voice connection is: connected
  - If connected: Send message via voice channel
  - If not connected: Add to message queue, ensure voice session starts

Behavior when mode is text:
  - Check if text connection is: connected
  - If connected: Send message via text channel
  - If not connected: Add to message queue, ensure text session starts

On success:
  - Message delivered to AI
  - Return: success

On error:
  - Message added to queue
  - Return: queued

[Action HandleIncomingMessage]
Description: Process messages received from AI

Execute if:
  Message received from: ElevenLabs API

Steps:
  - Determine message source: AI or user
  - Determine transport type: WebSocket or WebRTC
  - Extract message text content
  - Normalize message format
  - Notify registered message handlers
  - Save to conversation history
  - Update UI with new message

Message type detection:
  If event type: agent_response
    - Source: AI
    - Extract text from: agent_response field or message field
  
  If event type: user_transcript
    - Source: user
    - Extract text from: user_transcript field
  
  If unrecognized format:
    - Attempt to parse as string
    - Default source: AI

[Behavior CrossTabSessionLock]
Description: Prevent multiple tabs from having conflicting sessions

Storage: Browser localStorage
Key: elevenlabs_session_lock
Data stored:
  - conversationId: Active session ID
  - mode: text or voice
  - tabId: Which tab owns the lock
  - timestamp: When lock was acquired

Lock acquisition:
  When: Starting a new session
  Check: Is there existing lock
  If lock exists and not stale:
    - Deny session start
    - Show message: another tab has active session
  If no lock or lock is stale:
    - Acquire lock
    - Broadcast to other tabs
    
Lock release:
  When: Session ends
  When: Tab closes
  When: Session idle for too long

Staleness check:
  Lock is stale if: timestamp older than 30 seconds
  Purpose: Handle crashes or force-closed tabs

[Behavior IdleTimeout]
Description: Automatically close text sessions after inactivity

Apply to: Text sessions only
Timeout duration: 5 minutes

Timer reset when:
  - User sends message
  - User explicitly resets timer
  - Activity detected in session

When timeout triggers:
  - Run StopTextSession action
  - Show notification: session closed due to inactivity

[Behavior MessageQueue]
Description: Queue messages when connection unavailable

Queues:
  - Text message queue
  - Voice message queue

Add to queue when:
  - User sends message
  - Connection state: not connected
  - Connection state: connecting

Flush queue when:
  - Connection state becomes: connected
  - Send all queued messages in order
  - Clear queue after sending

Queue limit: 50 messages
If queue full: reject new messages with error
```

