NO synonyms! Same action = same verb ALWAYS
```

## Avoid Technical Jargon - Use Plain Language
```
❌ Initialize, init           → ✅ Create
❌ Apply, assign, mark, flag  → ✅ Set
❌ Flush, drain               → ✅ Send all
❌ Load, fetch, get           → ✅ Read
❌ invoke, trigger, execute   → ✅ Call (for named things) or Do (for processes)
❌ Display, render            → ✅ Show
❌ await, block until         → ✅ Wait for
❌ Acquire/take lock          → ✅ Set session owner: this tab
❌ Release lock               → ✅ Clear session owner
❌ log, trace, debug          → ✅ Save error details
❌ ref                        → ✅ internal tracking variable
❌ unmounted component        → ✅ component that was removed
❌ WebRTC peer connection     → ✅ voice connection
❌ WebSocket                  → ✅ text connection
❌ Arrow notation (→)         → ✅ Natural conditions

BUT: Use actual SDK parameter names like dynamicVariables, agentId, signedUrl
